comes at the end...

03:52.533 --> 03:54.266
After the ghosts.

03:54.268 --> 03:55.033
<i>I felt awful for lying,</i>

03:55.035 --> 03:58.971
<i>but how scary</i>
<i>could the movie really be?</i>

04:02.342 --> 04:05.377
<i>Turns out, it was scary!</i>

04:05.912 --> 04:08.180
<i>Really scary!</i>

04:11.384 --> 04:15.020
<i>Really, really scary!</i>

04:17.056 --> 04:19.491
(AUDIENCE MURMURING)

04:21.995 --> 04:25.330
Where the (BLEEP)
was the mouse?

04:25.332 --> 04:28.467
Okay, so you got
your love seats
over there,

04:28.469 --> 04:31.136
uh, sectionals
over there.

04:31.138 --> 04:32.804
That's a divan.

04:32.806 --> 04:35.574
Hey, Vic, say hello
to my son.

04:35.576 --> 04:37.743
What? Little baby Barry?

04:37.745 --> 04:38.277
Get outta here!

04:38.279 --> 04:39.645
That's a good-looking
kid there, Mur.

04:39.647 --> 04:42.014
He must get it
from his mom! (LAUGHS)
(FORCED LAUGH)

04:42.016 --> 04:45.550
Where does Vic Jr.
get it from, Carl down
at the loading dock?

04:45.552 --> 04:47.352
Oh, man, come on!
(LAUGHS)

04:47.354 --> 04:49.454
That's part of the job.
We bust balls.

04:49.456 --> 04:51.757
Yeah, Vic.
You sad old loser.

04:51.759 --> 04:52.591
(LAUGHS)
Hey, what?

04:52.593 --> 04:54.626
You know what?
He's new. He's new.

04:54.628 --> 04:57.062
Let's just get to work.
All right.

04:57.064 --> 04:59.531
So this is what we do
all day?

04:59.533 --> 05:01.700
It's pretty cool.
No, no, no, no.

05:01.702 --> 05:04.770
This is what I do
all day, okay?

05:04.772 --> 05:05.837
You sweep.

05:05.839 --> 05:08.073
And then you move
some furniture,

05:08.075 --> 05:09.508
and you sweep around that.

05:09.510 --> 05:10.475
I'll see you for lunch.

05:10.477 --> 05:13.979
Ah. I see what you're
trying to do.

05:13.981 --> 05:15.047
You're trying to break me.

05:15.049 --> 05:17.716
Well, you can't break me,
old man.

05:17.718 --> 05:19.351
I'll sweep your floor,
and you know why?

05:19.353 --> 05:23.789
'Cause nobody
gets to the NBA
without a struggle.

05:24.090 --> 05:26.291
(EXHALES)
Struggle away.

05:28.394 --> 05:30.662
Vic? A little help here?

05:30.664 --> 05:31.496
Hell, no.

05:31.498 --> 05:32.397
(RATTLING)
(WIND WHISTLING)

05:32.399 --> 05:34.199
<i>Sure, I knew</i> Poltergeist
<i>was just a movie...</i>
<i>(TAPPING)</i>

05:34.201 --> 05:39.171
<i>But when night came,</i>
<i>it seemed pretty</i>
<i>freakin' real!</i>

05:43.576 --> 05:45.544
(CACKLING)

05:46.012 --> 05:48.447
(CACKLING CONTINUES)

05:48.748 --> 05:49.815
(CACKLING FADES)

05:49.817 --> 05:51.783
I just can't stop thinking
about that movie.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.518
It's really gone
to my head, Pops.

05:53.520 --> 05:56.822
Aw, buddy.
It's all make-believe.

05:56.824 --> 05:57.956
<i>It's not.</i>

05:57.958 --> 05:58.924
Ghosts are real.

05:58.926 --> 06:00.792
They're what keep
the Ghostbusters employed.

06:00.794 --> 06:03.695
<i>You got nothing to be</i>
<i>afraid of.</i>

06:03.697 --> 06:06.198
Now go get some rest.

06:06.200 --> 06:08.400
Okay. Good night.

06:09.102 --> 06:10.268
<i>In my head,</i>
<i>I knew Pops was right,</i>

06:10.270 --> 06:14.406
<i>but the rest of me was not</i>
<i>gonna take any chances.</i>

06:14.408 --> 06:16.675
(BUTTON CLICKS)
(WHIRRING)

06:16.677 --> 06:19.478
<i>Desperate times called</i>
<i>for desperate measures.</i>

06:19.480 --> 06:22.080
(WHISPERING) Mom?
I have a tummy ache.

06:22.082 --> 06:26.151
(LOWERED VOICE)
Oh, sweetie.
Do you need to make?

06:26.285 --> 06:28.186
No! But...

06:28.287 --> 06:30.322
Can I sleep here tonight?

06:30.324 --> 06:32.157
Yeah, sure.

06:35.661 --> 06:36.294
<i>I had given in.</i>

06:36.296 --> 06:38.830
<i>For one night, my mom</i>
<i>would get the snuggles</i>

06:38.832 --> 06:41.900
<i>she so desperately craved.</i>

06:44.303 --> 06:45.404
<i>And then morning came.</i>

06:45.406 --> 06:49.141
How's the tum-tum?
It's fine. I'm fine.

06:49.475 --> 06:51.243
I gotta go.

06:53.279 --> 06:54.179
See ya!

06:54.181 --> 06:54.813
(SCOFFS) Okay.

06:54.815 --> 06:57.215
(DOOR OPENS)
Oh, Adam, you forgot
your jacket.

06:57.217 --> 06:59.518
Don't need it!
(DOOR CLOSES)

07:00.653 --> 07:01.253
<i>"Poltergeist"?</i>

07:01.255 --> 07:05.657
I told him not to see
that movie. Unbelievable!

07:05.858 --> 07:06.925
He's scared.

07:06.927 --> 07:08.860
That's why he wants
snuggies.

07:08.862 --> 07:10.996
Hey, if you're looking
for some snuggies, I...

07:10.998 --> 07:11.963
You're not going
to that party.

07:11.965 --> 07:15.033
You never let me do...
(CLENCHES TEETH)
Anything!

07:15.701 --> 07:16.568
Ugh!

07:16.570 --> 07:17.669
<i>That's when my mom realized</i>

07:17.671 --> 07:19.638
<i>she had found the ticket</i>
<i>to all the snuggies</i>

07:19.640 --> 07:22.174
<i>she could ever want.</i>
<i>(DOOR CLOSES)</i>

07:23.843 --> 07:25.610
(DOOR CREAKS)

07:30.550 --> 07:31.249
Mom?

07:31.251 --> 07:34.419
You didn't put
this clown here, did you?

07:34.421 --> 07:35.253
Yes, Adam.

07:35.255 --> 07:37.456
After running errands,
cooking dinner,

07:37.458 --> 07:39.458
and cleaning the house,
I had lots of time

07:39.460 --> 07:40.892
to futz around
with a clown.

07:40.894 --> 07:43.395
Okay, okay. Jeez.

07:43.397 --> 07:46.298
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

07:53.473 --> 07:56.308
Mom? I have a tummy ache!

07:56.310 --> 08:00.078
<i>Little did I know</i>
<i>the scariest thing</i>
<i>in this house</i>

08:00.080 --> 08:03.014
<i>was lying right next to me.</i>

08:04.917 --> 08:06.785
<i>After a grueling week</i>
<i>of manual labor,</i>

08:06.787 --> 08:11.156
<i>the day Barry had been</i>
<i>waiting for had arrived...</i>

08:11.158 --> 08:12.891
<i>Payday.</i>

08:13.993 --> 08:17.095
$33.27?

08:17.530 --> 08:20.098
Is this some sick joke?

08:20.533 --> 08:21.566
Oh.

08:21.568 --> 08:23.768
You're just busting balls,
huh?

08:23.770 --> 08:25.370
This is a joke paycheck.

08:25.372 --> 08:27.205
I wish I was
busting balls.

08:27.207 --> 08:27.973
Welcome to
the real world.

08:27.975 --> 08:31.576
I know I made
more than this.
Why is it so low?

08:31.578 --> 08:32.744
Taxes!

08:32.746 --> 08:35.914
You got federal, state,
Social Security, FICA.

08:35.916 --> 08:39.985
What are you talking about?
Those aren't real things.

08:39.987 --> 08:40.752
Did you ever go
to school?

08:40.754 --> 08:42.921
Taxes? Those are
totally real things.

08:42.923 --> 08:44.256
Just let me become
a salesman.

08:44.258 --> 08:46.358
I can make more if I work
on commission.

08:46.360 --> 08:48.293
You? You're not ready.

08:48.295 --> 08:49.828
There's a customer
right there.

08:49.830 --> 08:51.429
Just let me go sell him
the pink couch?

08:51.431 --> 08:52.931
It's a salmon love seat.

08:52.933 --> 08:55.567
It's been there
for five years.

08:55.569 --> 08:56.368
In un-sellable.

08:56.370 --> 08:58.103
I'm gonna move him
over to the sectionals.

08:58.105 --> 09:02.173
You stay over here
and continue your
fine broom work.

09:04.143 --> 09:07.579
Sir, just so you know,
we have financing.

09:07.581 --> 09:10.248
Bad credit, no credit...
No problem.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.617
Thanks. I'm not gonna
make any final decisions
today, so...

09:12.619 --> 09:15.086
Today is not a day
for final decisions.

09:15.088 --> 09:18.456
I'm with you.
Take your time.

09:18.458 --> 09:21.159
What are you doing?
Sorry.
I had a phone call.

09:21.161 --> 09:22.260
I didn't hear
the phone ring.

09:22.262 --> 09:25.163
Oh, it rang.
It was Ron Jaworski.

09:25.165 --> 09:26.831
Said he wants this couch.

09:26.833 --> 09:29.935
Ron Jaworski?
The Eagles quarterback?

09:30.069 --> 09:31.603
Dude.

09:32.171 --> 09:34.272
(CHUCKLES) Dude!
Dude!

09:34.373 --> 09:35.240
Dude.
Dude?

09:35.242 --> 09:39.477
Dude. He literally
just called.

09:39.545 --> 09:40.645
I want this couch.

09:40.647 --> 09:42.280
Mmm... No can do.

09:42.282 --> 09:44.382
Ronnie J. just put
this on reserve.

09:44.384 --> 09:45.984
What if I pay cash?

09:46.819 --> 09:48.286
Murray?

09:50.923 --> 09:54.125
You know what?
I'll handle Big Ron.

09:54.127 --> 09:56.394
You, sir, have got
yourself a deal.

09:56.396 --> 09:58.196
(GASPS) Thank you.

09:58.198 --> 10:00.298
<i>No doubt about it.</i>
<i>Barry was a natural.</i>

10:00.300 --> 10:04.703
<i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>I was still dealing</i>
<i>with the supernatural.</i>

10:04.705 --> 10:06.071
(TV TURNS ON)

10:06.073 --> 10:08.473
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

10:08.475 --> 10:10.342
(STATIC HISSING)

10:12.912 --> 10:15.046
(STATIC HISSING)

10:19.185 --> 10:19.751
(SHIVERING)

10:19.753 --> 10:21.319
(DOOR CLOSES)
(PANTING) Mom...

10:21.321 --> 10:24.055
Oh! What's this about?
(GASPS)

10:24.057 --> 10:26.925
(WHISPERS)
Tummy ache.
Okay.

10:27.026 --> 10:28.660
Why don't you, uh,
run upstairs,

10:28.662 --> 10:31.229
and I'll be there
in a minute, okay?
(EXHALES)

10:31.231 --> 10:32.998
It's fine.

10:35.234 --> 10:35.867
Wow!

10:35.869 --> 10:36.868
(DOOR CLOSES)
(GROANS)

10:36.870 --> 10:39.537
You scared me.
That's not cool.

10:39.539 --> 10:43.775
Not cool, huh? Why'd you
take the remote outside?

10:43.777 --> 10:44.743
It's not what you think.

10:44.745 --> 10:48.880
I think you're scaring Adam
so he'll give you hugs.

10:48.882 --> 10:50.882
It might be what you think.

10:50.884 --> 10:52.117
But is that so wrong?

10:52.119 --> 10:55.286
Yes, it's wrong!
Very, very wrong.

10:55.288 --> 10:56.321
Well, it would have
never come to this

10:56.323 --> 11:00.458
if I didn't have to beg
for affection
from my own children.

11:00.460 --> 11:01.026
Here we go.

11:01.028 --> 11:02.093
I used to walk
through that door,

11:02.095 --> 11:05.497
and you would
all come running
and jump into my arms.

11:05.499 --> 11:08.700
And then you stopped.
And Barry stopped.

11:08.702 --> 11:10.802
Adam's all I have left.
And if he stops,

11:10.804 --> 11:12.203
no one's ever gonna
hug me again.

11:12.205 --> 11:15.407
(SCOFFS)
You know I'm gonna have
to tell Adam, right?

11:15.409 --> 11:15.840
Don't!

11:15.842 --> 11:20.612
Just one more night of snugs,
and I'll never do it again.
I promise.

11:20.614 --> 11:23.314
I suppose I could forget
the whole thing

11:23.316 --> 11:26.317
if you let me stay out
insanely late this weekend.

11:26.319 --> 11:27.085
Deal.
Really?

11:27.087 --> 11:28.486
Please. Like you
were gonna come home

11:28.488 --> 11:31.156
when I wanted anyway?
True.

11:31.757 --> 11:32.624
I feel good about this.

11:32.626 --> 11:34.726
<i>My mother wasn't</i>
<i>the only one feeling good.</i>

11:34.728 --> 11:36.494
<i>Over the next week,</i>
<i>Barry proved himself to be</i>

11:36.496 --> 11:40.231
<i>not only a great salesman,</i>
<i>but a real visionary.</i>
<i>(TELEPHONE RINGING)</i>

11:40.233 --> 11:42.600
Mix the duck sauce
with the hot mustard

11:42.602 --> 11:43.802
and dip your egg roll
in it.

11:43.804 --> 11:45.770
That's crazy!
Who does that?

11:45.772 --> 11:49.808
Just do it.
You'll like it,
you big baby.

11:49.975 --> 11:51.676
(CRUNCHES)

11:51.777 --> 11:53.645
I don't like it.

11:54.380 --> 11:55.013
I love it!

11:55.015 --> 11:56.548
Hey, Barry, there's
a woman on the phone

11:56.550 --> 11:58.717
who said that you set aside
two nightstands for her?

11:58.719 --> 12:02.320
Yep. And set aside
a one-night stand
for your wife.

12:02.322 --> 12:03.388
Wha...

12:03.390 --> 12:05.090
Just busting balls.

12:05.092 --> 12:06.257
It's what we do.

12:06.259 --> 12:09.728
Come on. (LAUGHS)
That's what we do.

12:10.329 --> 12:11.329
