12:14.867 --> 12:15.900
<i>But my dad began to notice</i>

12:15.902 --> 12:18.803
<i>that success</i>
<i>was changing Barry,</i>

12:18.805 --> 12:22.040
<i>and not all for the good.</i>

12:22.042 --> 12:22.941
(SIGHS)

12:22.943 --> 12:24.242
That's the stuff.

12:24.244 --> 12:25.043
What the hell
are you doing?

12:25.045 --> 12:29.514
Get out of my chair,
go outside, play basketball.

12:29.516 --> 12:30.548
Or something.

12:30.550 --> 12:31.916
Ah, screw basketball.

12:31.918 --> 12:34.285
It was a stupid dream.
You were right.

12:34.287 --> 12:37.789
But furniture?
That's where it's at.

12:37.791 --> 12:39.724
Oh, look at you!

12:39.726 --> 12:42.827
Ha ha!
You're a mini Murray!

12:42.829 --> 12:45.396
Chip off the old block.

12:46.499 --> 12:47.098
<i>He really was,</i>

12:47.100 --> 12:50.268
<i>and my dad suddenly realized</i>
<i>he didn't like it one bit.</i>

12:50.270 --> 12:54.672
<i>So he decided to handle it</i>
<i>the only way he knew how.</i>

12:54.674 --> 12:56.040
You're fired.

12:56.042 --> 12:57.642
What? Why?

12:57.644 --> 12:58.409
It's not working out.

12:58.411 --> 13:01.079
Yes, it is.
It's working out awesome.

13:01.081 --> 13:02.714
You just can't randomly
fire me.

13:02.716 --> 13:04.015
I mean,
you have to have cause.

13:04.017 --> 13:07.352
Okay. It's 'cause
you're a moron.

13:07.354 --> 13:08.887
No. This is not happening.

13:08.889 --> 13:13.091
In fact, I fire you.
That's right, you're fired.

13:13.093 --> 13:14.759
You don't have to go.
No. No, no, no.

13:14.761 --> 13:16.094
You guys leave and come
to my store instead.

13:16.096 --> 13:18.296
He doesn't have a store.
Oh, yes,
I do have a store.

13:18.298 --> 13:20.231
I'm opening one
right across the street.

13:20.233 --> 13:21.866
He's not opening
across the street.

13:21.868 --> 13:23.268
I just did!
No, you didn't.

13:23.270 --> 13:25.603
And Ron Jaworski's
really gonna go there...

13:25.605 --> 13:26.805
You don't know
Ron Jaworski.

13:26.807 --> 13:28.873
And people are gonna
treat each other nicely.

13:28.875 --> 13:32.577
It's gonna be a friendly
working environment!

13:32.579 --> 13:35.580
Who's coming
with me, huh?

13:35.681 --> 13:36.581
You! Vic,

13:36.583 --> 13:39.450
I'm doubling your salary.
You work for me now.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.686
Wait, for real?
For real, for real.

13:41.688 --> 13:43.888
No, he's not going
with you.

13:43.890 --> 13:45.723
Toodle-oo!

13:46.725 --> 13:47.959
His store sounds nice.

13:47.961 --> 13:50.995
His store isn't real!
(DOOR CLOSES)

13:52.464 --> 13:55.166
<i>My dad was hoping</i>
<i>by the time he got home</i>
<i>from work,</i>

13:55.168 --> 13:56.935
<i>the Barry incident</i>
<i>would have blown over.</i>

13:56.937 --> 14:00.138
<i>But in our house,</i>
<i>things just blow up.</i>

14:00.140 --> 14:02.340
You fired your own son?

14:02.342 --> 14:03.174
Oh, boy.

14:03.176 --> 14:04.709
Damn right he fired me.

14:04.711 --> 14:07.812
And you know why?
'Cause he's jealous.

14:07.814 --> 14:10.415
That's right.
I sold the pink couch.

14:10.417 --> 14:11.149
And for a brief moment,

14:11.151 --> 14:14.652
you got to see what
a good furniture salesman
looks like.

14:14.654 --> 14:17.255
This. Yeah. soak it in.

14:17.257 --> 14:21.693
Okay. We're done yelling.
Let's all just calm down.

14:21.695 --> 14:22.427
Oh, I'm done.

14:22.429 --> 14:25.129
I'm done with you,
I'm done with the store,

14:25.131 --> 14:27.065
and I'm done
with furniture... Forever!

14:27.067 --> 14:29.968
What does that even mean?
I reject all furniture!

14:29.970 --> 14:32.804
I'm going up to my room
and getting rid of everything.

14:32.806 --> 14:35.673
I'll never be
comfortable again.

14:38.244 --> 14:40.411
(WHEELS RATTLING ON GROUND)

14:48.020 --> 14:48.753
What are you doing?

14:48.755 --> 14:52.223
Rejecting all furniture.
What are you doing?

14:52.225 --> 14:54.893
There's a ghost
in the TV.

14:54.895 --> 14:56.461
That's just stupid.

15:00.966 --> 15:02.700
Thanks for sleeping over,
Pops.

15:02.702 --> 15:05.103
I'm sorry I didn't come
sooner, kiddo.

15:05.105 --> 15:08.940
No man should have to
bunk up with his mom
for a week.

15:08.942 --> 15:09.474
No man.

15:09.476 --> 15:11.142
But what happens
when you leave?

15:11.144 --> 15:12.944
You can't protect me
forever.

15:12.946 --> 15:15.513
But this watch sure can.

15:15.515 --> 15:19.584
My grandpa Irv gave me this
just before I shipped off
to France,

15:19.586 --> 15:22.720
and he told me
as long as I kept it
with me,

15:22.722 --> 15:26.457
nothing bad would happen,
and he was right.

15:26.459 --> 15:27.859
Boom.

15:27.861 --> 15:28.960
(EXHALES)

15:28.962 --> 15:31.029
Thanks.
I feel better already.

15:31.031 --> 15:34.065
(VOICE WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY)

15:34.067 --> 15:35.366
What the hell is that?

15:35.368 --> 15:36.501
(WHISPERING CONTINUES)

15:36.503 --> 15:38.303
It came from inside
the trunk.

15:38.305 --> 15:40.071
(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

15:40.073 --> 15:40.838
(IN DEEP VOICE) Evil!

15:40.840 --> 15:42.573
(WHISPERING) Beverly,
what are you doing?

15:42.575 --> 15:44.275
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

15:44.277 --> 15:45.977
(GASPS)
It keeps coming back!

15:45.979 --> 15:48.546
(PANTS)
There's gotta be a rational
explanation for this.

15:48.548 --> 15:52.784
Of course there is!
My toy chest is
a portal to hell!

15:52.786 --> 15:53.851
(WHISPERING RESUMES)

15:53.853 --> 15:58.022
Aha! That's the explanation!

15:58.024 --> 16:00.391
My walkie-talkie?

16:01.226 --> 16:02.593
You!
What's the matter, pooh?

16:02.595 --> 16:04.395
Don't you "pooh" me.
Don't you "pooh" him.

16:04.397 --> 16:07.999
There is a monster
in this house,
and it's you.

16:08.001 --> 16:09.567
You're the monster.

16:09.569 --> 16:11.703
If that's what you really
think of me,

16:11.705 --> 16:14.539
then I have failed
as a mother.

16:14.673 --> 16:16.441
(STATIC)

16:17.609 --> 16:19.344
Well, you lied, too.

16:19.346 --> 16:21.112
I told you not to see
that movie,

16:21.114 --> 16:21.813
and you did it anyway.

16:21.815 --> 16:24.382
And you shouldn't have
let him see something
so scary.

16:24.384 --> 16:28.186
Not my fault. That movie
was wildly mis-titled.

16:28.188 --> 16:31.289
There was neither a mouse
nor a detective.

16:31.291 --> 16:33.257
I hope you enjoyed the hugs
while they lasted,

16:33.259 --> 16:34.692
'cause I got news for you,
woman.

16:34.694 --> 16:37.528
As of this moment,
I'll never snug you again.

16:37.530 --> 16:39.130
Ever!

16:40.833 --> 16:43.067
<i>After a week of being scared</i>
<i>by my own mother,</i>

16:43.069 --> 16:47.138
<i>what I just said</i>
<i>terrified her to the core.</i>

16:47.140 --> 16:49.307
(SIGHS)
I can't believe
I'm losing sleep

16:49.309 --> 16:50.541
over that damn kid.

16:50.543 --> 16:51.976
(CLICKS TONGUE)
(SIGHS)

16:51.978 --> 16:52.944
Adam's never
forgiving me,

16:52.946 --> 16:56.080
but you could still patch
things up with Barry.

16:56.082 --> 16:57.982
Just hire him back.

16:58.083 --> 16:58.516
I can't!

16:58.518 --> 17:03.955
The last thing I want
is that kid peddling furniture
for the rest of his life.

17:03.957 --> 17:05.123
I want more for him.

17:05.125 --> 17:06.924
Why didn't you
tell him that?

17:06.926 --> 17:09.227
Eh, he... He knows.

17:09.229 --> 17:10.595
Murray.

17:10.597 --> 17:11.996
Fine!

17:12.231 --> 17:13.631
Fine.

17:14.833 --> 17:16.300
We're bad parents,
aren't we?

17:16.302 --> 17:19.604
We're not great,
that's for sure.

17:19.606 --> 17:21.839
But who really is?

17:21.907 --> 17:22.607
Well...

17:22.609 --> 17:26.110
Ah. The blond people
down the block.

17:26.112 --> 17:27.912
The ones
with all the bikes.

17:27.914 --> 17:29.680
They're making it work.

17:29.682 --> 17:33.084
Oh. At least we have
each other.

17:33.086 --> 17:36.054
Yeah, you can't
scare me away.

17:37.623 --> 17:39.390
(EXHALES)

17:45.731 --> 17:46.464
Here.

17:46.466 --> 17:49.700
I know you love Bill Murray
and you wanted
to see  <i>Stripes</i>

17:49.702 --> 17:51.502
and I wouldn't let you.

17:51.504 --> 17:54.238
Um... It's playing
at the Dollar Theater.

17:54.706 --> 17:56.374
Not interested.

17:56.442 --> 17:59.010
I hear they show boobs.

17:59.378 --> 18:01.079
How many?

18:01.547 --> 18:03.381
I'm sorry I scared you.

18:03.383 --> 18:07.118
But you were so warm
and snuggy, and...

18:07.120 --> 18:08.519
I miss it.

18:08.521 --> 18:12.056
I just need a hug,
and when I don't get it,

18:12.058 --> 18:14.192
I do bad things.

18:16.195 --> 18:17.295
Fine.

18:17.297 --> 18:19.030
One hug a week.

18:19.032 --> 18:21.999
One a day,
Monday through Friday,
weekends off.

18:22.001 --> 18:22.867
Every other day,
two seconds max.

18:22.869 --> 18:27.238
Five seconds.
Three and a half seconds.
That's my final offer.

18:27.240 --> 18:28.639
Deal.

18:29.374 --> 18:32.243
<i>(HERE I GO AGAIN</i> PLAYING)

18:44.189 --> 18:45.890
That one's free.

18:47.192 --> 18:49.460
(KNOCKS)
BARRY: What?

18:50.028 --> 18:52.396
Go away.
Not talking to you.

18:52.398 --> 18:55.533
That's okay.
I'll do the talking.

18:55.535 --> 18:58.503
Why? Did Mom send you here?

18:58.505 --> 19:00.304
Of course she did.

19:00.306 --> 19:05.109
All right. Uh...
When I was your age,

19:05.511 --> 19:09.080
my dad,
he wasn't around much.

19:09.082 --> 19:11.415
I had nobody looking out
for me.

19:11.417 --> 19:14.018
So I had no direction.

19:14.319 --> 19:16.020
Boy, if I hadn't met
your mother,

19:16.022 --> 19:18.689
I don't know
where I'd be today.

19:18.691 --> 19:22.693
And then Pops gave me
a job at the store,

19:22.695 --> 19:25.997
and, uh, suddenly I'm a guy

19:25.999 --> 19:29.233
with a family
and a future.

19:29.235 --> 19:30.601
What I'm trying to say is

19:30.603 --> 19:36.040
for me, selling furniture
was...was a big deal.

19:36.042 --> 19:38.376
But I want more for you.

19:40.712 --> 19:45.183
<i>♪ So I keep searching</i>
<i>for an answer</i>

19:45.751 --> 19:46.217
No.

19:46.219 --> 19:50.555
<i>♪ Never seem to find</i>
<i>what I'm looking for</i>

19:52.257 --> 19:54.025
No way.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.694
The Reebok Pumps?
For real?

19:56.696 --> 19:58.529
I thought you said
my dream was stupid.

19:58.531 --> 20:03.167
Yeah, well, you're just
the moron to pull it off.

20:03.169 --> 20:04.735
Oh, my goodness!

20:04.737 --> 20:07.471
<i>♪ The lonely street of dreams</i>

20:07.473 --> 20:12.009
<i>♪ And here I go again</i>
<i>on my own</i>

20:12.144 --> 20:17.582
<i>♪ Going down the only road</i>
<i>I've ever known</i>

20:17.816 --> 20:22.453
<i>♪ Like a drifter,</i>
<i>I was born to walk alone</i>

20:24.556 --> 20:28.059
<i>♪ And I've made up my mind</i>

20:29.261 --> 20:33.397
<i>♪ I ain't wastin'</i>
<i>no more time</i>

20:33.399 --> 20:34.265
(THUD)

20:34.267 --> 20:35.600
(MUSIC STOPS)
(GASPS)

20:35.602 --> 20:38.569
MURRAY: Thank God
he can sell furniture.

20:40.505 --> 20:42.974
<i>Welcome to my house.</i>

20:44.409 --> 20:45.476
(GRUNTING)

20:45.478 --> 20:48.179
<i>Ain't no one gonna</i>
<i>stop Barry. Uh!</i>

20:50.315 --> 20:52.350
<i>Swish, baby!</i>

20:54.620 --> 20:56.020
<i>Swish, baby!</i>

20:56.022 --> 20:57.955
<i>Lefty. Lefty.</i>

20:59.157 --> 21:01.092
<i>Swish, baby!</i>

21:06.465 --> 21:08.032
<i>Swish, baby!</i>

21:08.467 --> 21:10.334
<i>Basketball.</i>

21:13.805 --> 21:15.673
That was...
That was fantastic!

21:15.675 --> 21:20.344
He... He made a shot
from the end
of the driveway!

21:23.181 --> 21:24.682
Thank you.
